The paper discusses the integration of heterogeneous documents used in software development methods, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also proposes a formal refinement-based software development process, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) and software design (cs.SD). The use of a common system model and syntactic development steps also suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG).
